sense.name: physical force
sense.examples: the compressed gas exerts an increased pressure he used pressure to stop the bleeding That tank is under high pressure. I felt pressure on my face mask as I descended during the dive. With novocaine, patients only experience pressure, not pain, during dental procedures.

sense.name: social or emotional demands
sense.examples: the public brought pressure to bear on the government She felt constant pressure at her job. The pressure on him to win the Gold Medal was enormous.
